&lt;p&gt;Role: &lt;strong&gt;Salaried General Practitioner&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Hours: Up to 9 Sessions Weekly (part time will be considered)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Wolds View Primary Care Centre, Bridlington&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Permanent&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;£96,500 &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;City Health Care Partnership CIC is an innovative, award winning organisation, at the forefront of change and keen to recruit the best people to develop its services within the context of social business. We are seeking a dedicated and enthusiastic Salaried GP to work at Wolds View Primary Care Centre, Bridlington.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Wolds View Primary Care Centre is based at Bridlington Hospital and incorporates a GP Practice, Urgent Treatment Centre and GP Out Of Hours. The service area is also a “Hub” for Improving/Extended Access services.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role is to work within the GP Practice at Wolds View Primary Care Centre, providing high quality General Medical Services to the registered population of Wolds View GP Practice and supporting urgent care services, identifying health needs and achieve health gain for this population. The hours of work are up to 9 sessions weekly Monday-Friday between the hours of 0800-1830 but there is some flexibility on how these are worked.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is an exciting opportunity to work within a GP practice offering a full range of services and also in a busy health care environment alongside colleagues providing routine and urgent care to the community. This job will at times be challenging but enjoyable and rewarding.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An ability to commute within the organisation’s geographical area with access to an appropriate means of transport is also essential.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For informal enquiries please contact Anita Burnhill, Service Manager, Tel: 01262 425629 (email: anita.burnhill@nhs.net).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In cases when a vacancy receives a high number of applications, we may bring the closing date forward. You are therefore advised to submit your completed application as early as possible.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;All applications must be made through NHS Jobs Website.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;No agencies please&lt;/p&gt;
